# Vercel Web Analytics Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this React + Vite project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package using npm
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with resolved dependencies

### 2. Code Integration
Modified `/app/src/App.jsx`:
- Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/react";`
- Added `<Analytics />` component within the BrowserRouter context, after the Toaster component
- The Analytics component is now rendered on all pages of the application

## Implementation Details

According to the Vercel documentation for React/Vite projects, the Analytics component should be imported from `@vercel/analytics/react` and rendered within the application. I placed it at the root level of the App component to ensure it tracks all routes and pages.

The component was added after the Toaster component but within the RoutesContext.Provider to ensure it has access to the routing context while maintaining the existing code structure.

## Verification

✅ Build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
✅ Linter passed for App.jsx (no new errors introduced)
✅ All dependencies installed and lock files updated

## Next Steps

To complete the setup:
1. Enable Analytics in the Vercel dashboard for this project
2. Deploy the application to Vercel
3. Verify tracking by checking the Network tab for requests to the analytics endpoint after deployment
4. Monitor the Analytics dashboard after user traffic accumulates

## Files Modified
- `/app/package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `/app/package-lock.json` - Updated with resolved dependencies
- `/app/src/App.jsx` - Added Analytics component and import
